# S3 Storage Rules (Yandex Cloud)

## Configuration
- Use AWS SDK v3 (`@aws-sdk/client-s3`, `@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner`)
- Endpoint via env: `S3_ENDPOINT` (default: `https://storage.yandexcloud.net`)
- Region via env: `S3_REGION` (default: `ru-central1`)
- Credentials via env vars: `S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `S3_BUCKET`
- Public bucket URL var: `NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET` (for client-side URL construction)

## Upload Flow
1. Client requests presigned URL via API route (`/api/s3/presign`)
2. Server generates presigned PUT URL (expires in 10 min)
3. Client uploads directly to S3 via presigned URL
4. Client confirms upload, server saves file metadata to DB

## File Organization in Bucket
```
courses/{courseId}/lessons/{lessonId}/{filename}
homework/{submissionId}/{filename}
avatars/{userId}/{filename}
```

## Security
- Presigned URLs only for authenticated users
- Validate file type and size on client AND server
- Max file sizes: video 2GB, images 10MB, documents 50MB
- Only admins/curators can delete files

## Asset Manager (Admin)
- List objects with pagination using `ListObjectsV2Command`
- Preview images inline, video via player
- Attach existing assets to lessons without re-upload
